995) Open Court Publishing Company\nBULLET::::- Crick, Nathan. \"Democracy & Rhetoric: John Dewey on the Arts of Becoming\" (2010) University of South Carolina Press.\nBULLET::::- Fishman, Stephen M. and Lucille McCarthy. \"John Dewey and the Philosophy and Practice of Hope\" (2007). University of Illinois Press.\nBULLET::::- Garrison, Jim. \"Dewey and Eros: Wisdom and Desire in the Art of Teaching.\" Charlotte: Information Age Publishing, 2010. Original published 1997 by Teachers College Press.\nBULLET::::- Hickman, Larry A. \"John Dewey's Pragmatic Technology\" (1992). Indiana University Press.\nBULLET::::- Hook, Sidney. \"John Dewey: An Intellectual Portrait\" (1939)\nBULLET::::- Howlett, Charles F., and Audrey Cohan, eds. \"John Dewey: America's Peace-Minded Educator\" (Southern Illinois UP, 2016), 305 pp.\nBULLET::::- Kannegiesser, H. J. \"Knowledge and Science\" (1977). The Macmillan Company of Australia PTY Ltd.\nBULLET::::- Knoll, Michael (2009) From Kidd to Dewey: The Origin and Meaning of \"Social Efficiency\". \"Journal of Curriculum Studies\" 41 (June), 3, pp. 361–91.\nBULLET::::- Knoll, Michael (2014) Laboratory School, University of Chicago. D. C. Phillips (ed) \"Encyclopaedia of Educational Theory and Philosophy\", Vol. 2 (London: Sage), pp. 455–58.\nBULLET::::- Knoll, Michael (2014) John Dewey as Administrator: The Inglorious End of the Laboratory School in Chicago. \"Journal of Curriculum Studies\", 47 (April), 2, pp. 203–52.\nBULLET::::- Lamont, Corliss (1959), (ed., with the assistance of Mary Redmer). \"Dialogue on John Dewey\". Horizon Press\nBULLET::::- Morse, Donald J. \"Faith in Life: John Dewey's Early Philosophy.\" (2011). Fordham University Press\nBULLET::::- Pappas, Gregory. \"John Dewey's Ethics: Democracy as Experience.\" (2008) Indiana University Press.\nBULLET::::- Popkewitz, Thomas S. (ed). \"Inventing the Modern Self and John Dewey: Modernities and the Traveling of Pragmatism in Education.\" (2005) New York: Palgrave Macmillan.\nBUL